Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into 1-inch wedges, like steak fries. Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until tender and lightly crisped, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Halve, peel and mince @shallot{1}(minced). Trim @green beans{12%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium high heat. Pat @chicken breasts{24%ounce} dry with #paper towel{} and season on all sides with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add to pan and cook until no longer pink in center, about ~{5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan to rest.

While chicken cooks, toss green beans on another baking sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until slightly crispy, about ~{12%minutes}.

Add shallot, @thyme{1/4%ounce}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{} to pan used for chicken over medium heat. Toss until shallot is soft, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @balsamic vinegar{4%tablespoon} and @apricot jam{2%tablespoon}. Simmer until syrupy, about ~{1%minute}. Add @water{1/2%cup} and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Simmer until thickened, about ~{3%minutes}. Remove pan from heat and swirl in @butter{2%tablespoon}.

Discard thyme from pan and season sauce with salt and pepper. Thinly slice chicken and serve with green beans and potatoes. Drizzle pan sauce over chicken.